cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper deals with unsupervised generative models and disentangled representation learning, which are core topics in machine learning. The use of real-world datasets such as YouTube-Faces suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV), while the investigation of assumptions made by InfoGAN and the proposed modifications to address class imbalance suggest a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of latent factors of variation and the generative model approach also suggest a possible connection to neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the use of real-world datasets and the focus on image data suggest a possible connection to multimedia (cs.MM).
